Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper primarily deals with the hidden node problem in wireless networks and proposes solutions using different protocols and techniques. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper also discusses the virtual jamming problem, which is a security issue in wireless networks. 

3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper may involve some information theory concepts related to wireless communication and signal processing. 

4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a protocol booster (WiCCP) which involves system-level design and control. 

5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve some algorithmic solutions to the hidden node problem and virtual jamming problem.
